  "notes": "Pangasinan (Salitan Pangasinan), Northern Luzon (Malayo-Polynesian) language of the Philippines. Latin orthography: the 26 basic Latin letters plus the digraph ⟨ng⟩ /ŋ/. Native vocabulary has /a i ɨ u/ plus /ɛ ɔ/ largely in loans; the close central /ɨ/ is written ⟨e⟩ in the traditional spelling and ⟨ë⟩ in the revised one, so ⟨e⟩ carries both candidates. /tʃ dʒ ʃ/ occur chiefly in Spanish and English loans.",
